CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper January 14, 1956, pg. B24, reads: "'Carver Week' Choraleers - These young well-trained members of the Grace Memorial Presbyterian Church Choir were in excellent voice Monday night on Television Station WQED, when they appeared on the program which was part of the 'George Washington Carver Week' celebration. Included with the selections was the popular favorite, the 'Hallelujah Chorus.' - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Nan Moone Currington conducting Grace Memorial Presbyterian Church choir performing in WQED television station studio for George Washington Carver week celebration
